metadata.title: Social Web's infiltration of World Wide Web
metadata.description: Share of global websites* who link to Social Networks (in %)
metadata.main_insight: Facebook has the highest share of global websites linking to it, significantly more than other social networks.  A larger proportion of websites have links (All Links) to social networks compared to the percentage that just use plugins/widgets.

datafacts.annotation: The Units of All Links and Plugins/Widgets show a positive correlation.
datafacts.reason: The Pearson correlation coefficient of the Units between All Links and Plugins/Widgets is {r:.2f}, indicating a strong positive relationship.

datafacts.annotation: The Plugins/Widgets shows a sudden jump in Units from Google+ to facebook.
datafacts.reason: The Units for Plugins/Widgets increases from 13.3 at Google+ to 24.3 at facebook, indicating a sharp change.

datafacts.annotation: The All Links shows a sudden jump in Units from Google+ to twitter.
datafacts.reason: The Units for All Links increases from 21.5 at Google+ to 41.7 at twitter, indicating a sharp change.

datafacts.annotation: The All Links accounts for the majority in Google+.
datafacts.reason: The Units of All Links in Google+ accounts for 0.6178160919540231 (more than 50%) of the total of Units of all Traffic Source.

datafacts.annotation: The All Links accounts for the majority in facebook.
datafacts.reason: The Units of All Links in facebook accounts for 0.6698369565217391 (more than 50%) of the total of Units of all Traffic Source.

titles.sub_title: Share of global websites linking to Social Networks (by traffic source).
